#. [multiplayer]: id=Brotherhood_of_Light, role=illusion 0 ()}
msgid "Brotherhood of Light"
msgstr "Irmandade da Luz"

#. [multiplayer]: id=Brotherhood_of_Light, role=illusion 0 ()}
msgid ""
"Four white mages must roam the land performing good deeds and righting "
"wrongs in this non-linear multiplayer RPG adventure. Players must also work "
"together to discover the fate of the four lost brothers that went before. "
"This scenario features numerous sub-quests, a basic inventory and extensive "
"magic system.\n"
"\n"
"A co-operative multiplayer roleplaying scenario. Use map settings."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
msgid ""
"High in the jagged mountains, a sacred spring feeds the four rivers of "
"Alkabalst. It was here, many moons ago, that Maldor first glimpsed the "
"essence of light whilst meditating beneath the boughs of a great tree. It "
"was the first step on a journey towards the eternal light, towards an "
"understanding of creation itself. It was here that magic was born."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
msgid ""
"Years later, Maldor built a monastery on the site and founded an order of "
"mages dedicated to the pursuit of truth and enlightenment. Every four years, "
"four new apprentices travel to the monastery to study the ancient secrets of "
"white magic. Only thus are they ordained into the Brotherhood of Light."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
msgid ""
"To complete their training, however, these apprentices must eventually leave "
"the tranquility of the monastery and venture forth into the outside world. "
"Their task - to right wrongs, and bring light to where there is darkness. "
"Just as the cleansing waters of the sacred spring carries the power of the "
"great tree throughout the land, so too must the brotherhood go among the "
"peoples of the world as messengers of truth and bearers of the light."
msgstr ""

