#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid "Farewell, my brothers. May your good deeds purify these lands."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Farewell, Maldor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"Before you go, I must ask something more of you. It is an unusual request "
"and I am perhaps foolhardy to burden my apprentices with such a matter..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Tell us what troubles you, master."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"Four years ago, a party of mages set out from the monastery as you do today. "
"They were promising pupils, all four of them proficient in their field. But "
"alas, not one returned."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"I have heard no news of their whereabouts, nor indeed if they are still of "
"this earth. Now that you are to enter lands beyond the monastery, perhaps it "
"is right that you seek to learn the fate of the four apprentices that went "
"before you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"Their names were Paulos, Ultar, Romas and Goilop. Remember, it is only "
"because I have full faith in your purity of heart that I ask this of you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Thank you Maldor. We shall do as you request and seek out the four lost "
"brothers. Let there be light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#. [message]: id=Maldor
#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Let there be light!"
msgstr "Que haja Luz!"

