#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Trolls"
msgstr "Trogloditas"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Large cumbersome trolls roam the mountains of Alkabalst, it says here. We "
"should be wary of these violent oaths."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Gryphons"
msgstr "Grifos"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The majestic race of gryphons that could once be seen soaring above the "
"heights of the jagged mountains are now facing extinction, this book reports "
"- due to the increasing demand for their eggs in the rich trading towns."
msgstr ""

#
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Wolves"
msgstr "Lobos"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This book has a chapter on wolves. It seems much of the countryside is "
"blighted by these rabid animals."
msgstr ""

#
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Drakes"
msgstr "Dragos"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"There is a entry here about a race of creatures known as 'drakes' who are "
"said to be descended from the dragons of yore. Drakes are themselves rare "
"these days, however. The last to be seen in recent years were spotted in "
"Mount Sulphur in the north."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "*Finish Reading"
msgstr ""

#. [literal]
msgid "This book contains an epic poem entitled: 'The Folly of King Reulot'."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The late King Reulot was a powerful yet foolish ruler, who became convinced "
"of his own omnipotence. The poem ends rather tragically when the king orders "
"a castle - despite the advise of his courtiers - to be built on the "
"swampland east of Hayshore. The stubborn arrogance of the man meant he and "
"his subjects were killed when the castle inevitably collapsed into the swamp "
"waters. His ghost is said to still roam the area."
msgstr ""

#. [literal]
msgid "This weighty tome is some sort of encyclopedia."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Encyclopedia of Local Lore (2nd Edition)"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Castle Lyodus"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Apparently Castle Lyodus was once besieged during a long war with the "
"northern orcs. The king, however, has since enjoyed a reign of peace it "
"seems."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Mount Sulphur"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"According to this, the famed Sceptre of Fire is believed to reside in Mount "
"Sulphur, just north of Fokio City."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Fokio City"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"It says here the current ruler of Fokio City, Baron Grinn, won the key to "
"the city in a gambling tournament. The previous ruler had fallen on hard "
"times as a result of numerous orcish raids."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The Monastery of Light"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Whoever wrote this tome is a shamless heretic! Look what it says: 'The "
"Monastery of Light was built by a pious charlatan by the name of Maldor who "
"has subsequently founded a cult based on his paranoid superstitions...'"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Hayshore Market"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"There is lots here about an economic recession that afflicted Hayshore "
"Market some four years ago. Turgid stuff."
msgstr ""

