#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A sudden, piercing cry echoes across the mountains..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What was that?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "It sounded to me as if the voice conveyed a great sadness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Maybe we should investigate? It seemed to come from a short way to the West."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The gryphon barely notices you entering. She seems forlorn and distant."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Let us put the eggs back in their rightful place, this will brighten the "
"poor creature."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The cave is warm and musty, in the dim light you can see the great feathery "
"shape of a female gryphon. She is clearly distressed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"She suddenly notices you, lets out another horrific scream and prepares to "
"attack."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Halt! We mean no harm by entering your lair. What is it that causes you such "
"grief?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Your words seem to calm the animal. She backs off and gestures to the nests. "
"They are empty."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Her eggs have been taken, it seems, her children lost. We should endeavour "
"to aid this hapless creature."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Aye. We shall seek those who took her eggs, and we shall return them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Ah, it seems we have already encountered the thieves that raided these "
"nests. We should put the eggs back where they belong."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You place the eggs back in the nest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You place a couple of eggs securely into the nest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"This nest contains a couple of beautiful mauve eggs. You know from your "
"studies that gryphon eggs are considered a fine delicacy by many humans. "
"These would fetch a high price in one of the trading towns."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Leave the nest alone"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Steal the eggs"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You slip the eggs into your pouch unnoticed. You smile to yourself, knowing "
"you will soon be a rich man."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "There, the last of the eggs has been replaced."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The gryphon shuffles from nest to nest, checking the eggs and flapping her "
"wings. She then lets out another almighty cry. But this time it is a "
"heartwarming, joyous sound."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Finally, the gryphon turns to you. She presses her head against your ear and "
"whispers in an ancient tongue..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Farewell, Hrylon."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The gryphon lets out a final heartrending cry, collapses and falls silent."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "It's alright lads, it's only a monk."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"A group of men emerge from behind boulders. Although they do not seem openly "
"hostile, they grip the hilts of their weapons firmly. You note that one of "
"them is carrying an armful of large purple eggs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid "What do you want?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Bid them well and turn back"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Fine. Good day to you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "As soon as your back is turned the men flee."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Attack without warning"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You charge into combat unprovoked, hoping to catch Junko off-guard."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Offer to trade with them"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I see you are carrying gryphon eggs. Perhaps you would care to purchase some "
"more?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid ""
"You have more eggs? If you do, we would pay handsomely for another pair."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You produce the eggs from your pouch and Junko draws closer to inspect."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid ""
"Yep, it's a genuine golden-speckled. Now I shall relieve you of your wares!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Suddenly Junko and his men draw their weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Are they gryphon eggs you carry? It has been too long since I tasted such "
"fine foods - and I've always been especially fond of the purple variety. May "
"I buy them from you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "How much you got? I want 200 gold for the lot of them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I only have $bob.gold gold to offer you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Ha! That's a fraction of what I'll get at Hayshore market!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Nevertheless... I never turn my nose up at gold, however small a sum."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Junko smiles menacingly and gives a signal to his men. One by one they draw "
"their weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I can afford that price."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Very Well, it is a deal."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Junko hands over the eggs, takes the money and orders his men to move on."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Junko The Fox
msgid "Argg! You will pay..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Junko collapses, crushing the eggs beneath the weight of his lifeless body."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You take the eggs from Junko's body - fortunately they are all intact!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
msgid ""
"Ah, mountains trolls. I have read much about these creatures. What a delight "
"to finally meet some!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Gutt! Mraty-uw!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
msgid ""
"Such rudimentary communication, fascinating! Apparently their language "
"consists of less than forty phonetic sounds. It is a wonder they have "
"survived at all in these parts - yet according to dwarvish records they are "
"quite numbersome."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Brother, with all due respect for your learning, I fear this may not be the "
"appropriate time for such a discourse."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The troll scuttles towards you, grinning and yelping."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
msgid "I suppose not. Still, it is rather exciting to see them in the flesh."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You encounter a group of mages heading north. They are somewhat startled to "
"see you, but their manner is polite and reverent."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid "Greetings!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Greetings mage. Who are you and whither do you travel?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid ""
"Why, we go to the monastery. Me and my brothers are to become Mages of the "
"great Maldor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Ah, so you are this year's recruits eh? You have a taxing time ahead of you. "
"I am..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid "We know your name, brother. You are renowned among our kind."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"You have heard of me? My fortune is yet to be found, my work has barely "
"begun..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid ""
"And yet we know you will fare well, oh sagely brother. You and your "
"companions have our utmost respect."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"And I hope you fare well also, Dussel. But for now we must go. Maldor has "
"set us an urgent task."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid "Very well. Let there be light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The mages file past, nodding in silent deference."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Dussel, however, remains and speaks to you in a low whisper."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid ""
"I have been practising my magic in preparation, and, well, I would like to "
"bless you and your brothers if I may..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Dussel, only white mages are allowed to use Bless spells. You know that."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid "So, do you refuse my gift?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Dussel
msgid "Yes, be on your way"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Be on your way, precocious mage! It is folly to toy with magic beyond your "
"means - it is laid down in the code."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid ""
"Very well. I suppose your years of study have eroded your sense of "
"adventure. Goodbye."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Dussel
msgid "No, we would gladly accept your blessing"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"We would gladly accept your blessing, Dussel. I am honoured to receive your "
"gift."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid "Then I am honoured to bestow it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Dussel makes several furtive gestures with his hands and utters his words of "
"blessing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dussel
msgid "There, now I must catch up with the others."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Thank you, Dussel. Your talents are impressive. Keep it up."
msgstr ""

#. [spell]: id=bless
#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "Bless"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"This seems to be a library of some sort. It is quiet, and the fusty smell of "
"old leather-bound books pervades the air. You find the place comforting and "
"familiar."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Ha! We set forth on an adventure and here we are once more surrounded by "
"books!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Just then a librarian appears from behind a desk. Her manner is resigned and "
"sullen, yet also friendly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid "Greetings. I am Dionne of Werl. Welcome to my Library."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Greetings, Dionne. This seems like a fine collection. It is pleasing to find "
"that knowledge still has a place here in the outside world."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Alas, if only it were so. My readers are rare these days, and I run short on "
"funds. The library was once twice the size it is now, but in recent months I "
"have been forced to sell off all but the most important works."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Still, what remains is of good standard. Please feel free to browse. Of "
"course, I must charge the small fee of 3 gold per book..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Of course."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid "May I help you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. [option]: id=Dionne
msgid "Do you have any spell books here in the library?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Just the one, but it is nothing special. I used to own an original dwarven "
"spellbook a long time ago, but I was forced to sell it - along with a rather "
"wonderful volume of elven etchings."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Shame."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. [option]: id=Dionne
msgid "How reliable are your tomes?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Entirely. They are faithful and accurate in every sense, why the "
"Encyclopedia was even checked by Maldor himself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "That is proof enough for me, thank you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. [option]: id=Dionne
msgid "Have any other white mages crossed your path of late?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid "Um, no. Not that I can remember. Why?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"We are searching for our Brothers. It is possible they passed this way some "
"four years ago."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Maybe you should go ask Angus. He mentioned something about a mage's journal "
"a while back. Angus is one of my regular readers, he's a bit of a recluse "
"really but he can be trusted. He lives in the woods just east of here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Thank you, Dionne. Let us go see Angus then."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"You asked me that earlier. All I know is that Angus mentioned something "
"about a journal. If you haven't already, you should go and see him. The road "
"to the southeast leads to his house."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. [option]: id=Dionne
msgid "Is there some way we could help you to keep the library open?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Well, I'm always happy to accept donations. In fact I've just sent a bundle "
"of books to be sold at the market in Hayshore. If I could raise 60 gold I "
"could buy them back..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Do you want to make a donation to the library?"
msgstr ""

