#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Yes"
msgstr "Sim"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I have ample funds. Here, you may have your 60 gold. It would sadden me to "
"see this place close."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid "Really? Oh my!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"A wide smiles spread across Dionne's face. She runs to her desk, pulls out a "
"big ledger and starts scribbling with a pencil."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Thank you, thank you. Hmm, let's see... That means I can get the anthology "
"of poems back, the orcish dictionary - and maybe even that translation of "
"Delfador's memoirs..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You place the gold on the desk and leave the librarian to it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Actually, I'm afraid I don't have enough gold to help you buy back those "
"books. Maybe when I do I will return."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid "Ah, well."
msgstr ""

#
# File: Return_from_Captivity/scenarios/05_The_Land_of_the_Dragons.cfg, line: 356
