#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "No"
msgstr "Não"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I'm afraid I can't help you. I need what funds I have for the journey ahead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid "I see. Well, nevermind."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dionne
msgid ""
"Your generosity is boundless, but you have already done quite enough. Thank "
"you."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Baron Grinn
#. [option]: id=Dionne
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
#. [option]: speaker=unit
msgid "Nevermind"
msgstr "Esquece"

#. [option]: speaker=unit
msgid "Pay 3 gold to read the book"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=unit
msgid "I cannot afford it"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The stench of rotting flesh hits your nostrils. There are dead, decomposing "
"bodies lying strewn about the land."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Argg, what is this noisome odour? It is an offence I have not suffered in "
"all my days!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"There is much we have not suffered, my Brother. This is the smell of death - "
"the natural order of things."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"It looks as if some battle took place here not two suns ago. Of course, by "
"rights, we should bury these corpses."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"What?! You mean to touch these carcasses? I fear I do not have the stomach "
"for it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Alas, we must - it is written in the code. We must bury these fallen "
"fighters, and in doing so we must not defile their bodies. They go to "
"another place."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I suppose we must do as our law commands. But let us not tally! Whoever "
"dealt this death could well return in search of more."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "What do you want to do?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Conduct burial"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You bury the body and give a short prayer."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Search the body"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Mayor Jolleson
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Nothing"
msgstr "Nada"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "These doors are firmly locked, perhaps by some form of magic."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Suddenly the door in the mountain swings open and a large, vicious spider "
"lurches forward. Its fangs glisten with sticky poisonous saliva..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I knew it was folly to wait here!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "At least we have discovered the perpetrator of this foul massacre..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Brothers! Now is not the time to deal judgement or justice. Now is the time "
"to run!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A horseman approaches, riding hard on his steed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gladdyon
msgid ""
"Brothers! I am glad to have found you after such a short ride. King Lyodus "
"has requested you attend his court."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gladdyon
msgid ""
"He is at his castle, on the southern shore of Lake Jesaro. The road will "
"lead to it. Please come at once."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Without waiting for an answer, Gladdyon turns his horse and is gone."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Hmm. The King is a just man by all accounts, but do we have time to visit "
"his lordship?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Percy
msgid "Welcome to Castle Lyodus. The king is expecting you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gontul The Wise
msgid ""
"Please refrain from perusing my papers. They are of no concern of yours."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Andy
#. [message]: id=Arthur
#. [message]: id=Bob
#. [message]: id=Boris
#. [message]: id=Donald
#. [message]: id=Harry
#. [message]: id=Mark
#. [message]: id=Torquelle
msgid "At your command, sir!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jippo
msgid ""
"Hey! You slayed Jippo's brother! He try escape... you kill him. Now I kill "
"you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jippo
msgid "Hey you! Stop! Are the white men wot helped my brother Pocko?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Yes I believe we are. Pocko has found a new life on the far shore of Lake "
"Jesaro."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jippo
msgid "Jippo thanks you. Jippo gonna go there too..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The goblins scuttle to the shore and set off on rafts."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What happened here?! The ground is strewn with goblin corpses..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"Yes, oh wise brother. I was not happy about the goblins living so close to "
"the town, but I tolerated it. After you left, however, more of the vile "
"creatures came from across the lake also hoping to set up camp here. It was "
"too much."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"Your benelovent wisdom seemed to be full of holes. When another troupe of "
"goblins arrived I became convinced it was all a devious orcish plot. Me and "
"my men cut them down while they worked..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"You have gone back on your word, Gerridan. I am saddened as much by that as "
"by the sight of blood spilt needlessly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"It is goblin blood, and thus of no import. Now, please leave the town. You "
"are no longer welcome in Borol."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "Greetings, men of the monastery. I knew you would not fail me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The aged king speaks slowly as if a terrible weariness rests upon him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Greetings. What troubles you, King Lyodus?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"In short, orcs. My troubles, I'm afraid, tend always to take an orcish form."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"You are not alone in this. My studies have taught me much about these brown-"
"skinned foes. It seems they are a threat to many in these parts."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"You are correct, mage, but the orcs that dwell in books are but nothing to "
"those that mass on the other side of the great lake."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Alas, only when you have crossed swords with an orc will you truly know of "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Only when you have cut one down will you know how dark their blood runs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "Only when you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Okay. Your point is clear, King Lyodus, but your intention is not. Why did "
"you summon us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Ever since I took the throne the orcs of the north have been a curse to this "
"kingdom. I am not a violent man by nature, but history will remember my "
"reign as a time of war..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Only once has the fighting ceased. Four years ago we managed to drive back "
"the orcish hordes. They took flight and headed north into the beyond."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"In my foolishness, I believed the battle was won. I allowed my people to "
"return to the land, to seek out a normal life."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"It was meant to be the end of an era. The start of a new age of plenty. But "
"it was not to be."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Last winter the orcs returned in force. Within two weeks they had retaken "
"most of our key strongholds. Now, I am afraid to say, they control all the "
"lands north of Lake Jesaro."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, under the leadership of General Goiun we have managed to hold "
"Ahingtu - a small port just south of an orc encampment. He was a fine "
"warrior, Goiun, a veteran of the old days. But a recent raid saw him slain."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Our only hope is to launch a counter-attack. The bulk of my army has marched "
"West. In a week or two they will be in position to outflank the orcs. But in "
"the meantime we need a distraction, and for that my men need a new leader."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"I still have a few fights left in me, but I must remain here - to guard the "
"castle in case they attack by water."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"A new leader? Surely it is a warrior you seek, not a mage. Like you said, I "
"have never even seen an orc - let alone seen the color of their blood."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The king smiles wanly and rises from his chair."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "Yes, you are a mage. I have read much of your powers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"And I know the confidence your kind can instill in even the most shattered "
"of armies."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"It is you and your brothers who shall lead the troops at Ahingtu. It is you "
"that shall lay seige to the orc encampment."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "It is you who shall deal the first blow in this - the final struggle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Very well, we accept your task. It is our duty not to run from evil, but "
"confront it. We will fight."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The king's eyes brighten. Hope flows into his ravaged face."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "Thank you. My ships shall take you to Ahingtu. May the day be ours!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Board the ship"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You board the vessel and give the command to set sail."
msgstr ""

#
#. [message]: speaker=Harry
msgid "Who goes there?"
msgstr "Quem vem aí?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I am from the Brotherhood of Light. We have been sent by King Lyodus - he "
"has given us command of this garrison."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Donald
msgid ""
"Then we wait upon your orders, sir. May the Brotherhood bring light to this "
"dark land."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Harry
msgid "Indeed. You are just in time - the orcs are already mounting an attack!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Bob
msgid ""
"But beware the forests! The orcs have sent their assassins to lurk in the "
"woods and ambush anyone who dares approach their camp!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Very well, then prepare for battle my friends. We will not stop until we "
"have purged this evil."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "Do you bear news of victory?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I'm afraid not, Lyodus. We have yet to take the orc encampment."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "Again, I wish you luck."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Zanaibar
msgid ""
"So I am to be beaten by mages eh? I shall not suffer the same fate as my "
"brethren."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Zanaibar
msgid "It is you who shall perish!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Zanaibar
msgid "Damn you! Urhg..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
msgid "The orc leader is slain. Victory is ours!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Brothers, our work is here is done. The men of Lyodus fought well this day. "
"Let them be the ones to celebrate."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: role=lyodus_soldier
msgid ""
"No, you do yourself a disservice. Without your guidance we wouldn't have had "
"the courage to face this day."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "In any case we must be going..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: role=lyodus_soldier
msgid ""
"Make sure you speak to the king. He will be greatly gladdened by the news. "
"His men should remain to secure the area. Farewell."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "We have returned, Lyodus. The encampment has been taken."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"You are indeed men of honour. And I knew you would not return without news "
"of victory. If my judgement is true, then the orcs will march South to "
"retake the encampment. My troops in the West should then be able to attack, "
"undetected from the rear."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"I believe you have struck a decisive blow in this war - much like your "
"brothers before you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I do not understand you, King Lyodus. My order has never waged war with the "
"orcs..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"You see there are some things you do not know. When we routed the orcs four "
"years ago, it was not I that led my men to victory."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"It was your brothers who turned the tide of that battle. The four white "
"mages from the monastery..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Aha! We have been sent to discover what become of them. This is good news "
"indeed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Well, I am afraid not. Your brothers fought with honour and courage, but not "
"all survived the conflict. One of them, I am sad to say, was slain in the "
"final stages of the campaign. Goilop was his name. We honour his memory "
"still..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"So Goilop is dead? Ah, tis a noble end I suppose. But why did you not tell "
"us this before?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"I do apologise for my deceit - I meant no malice by it. I merely feared that "
"news of Goilop's death would deter you from following in his footsteps. I "
"was desperate for your help, I am sorry..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"We forgive you for that, King Lyodus. But you should not have doubted our "
"bravery. If Goilop died for this cause, then we are pleased to have "
"furthered it also."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Again, I apologise. I now know that you and your kind are as versed with "
"battle as you are with books. You are remarkable men, and have my ever-"
"lasting gratitude."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, I feel obliged to reward you with something a little more "
"tangible. Here..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "At the king's request his men drag forth several treasure chests."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"I know a mage has little desire for gold, but maybe it will be useful now "
"that you go amongst those who you do."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Also, I have asked my magician to concoct a few drinks for you. Please, "
"accept my gifts, and may all be well with you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Thank you and farewell..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The potion restores you to full mana."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Sidney Trott
msgid ""
"Halt! Where do you think you're going? Turn over your gold, or I'll clobber "
"you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "What will you do?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Hand over all your gold"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Men like you are a scourge on this land. Have your precious gold and be gone."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Sidney Trott
msgid "Thank you. That'll do nicely..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The bandit scuttles off into the mountains."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Attack him"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "You are an oaf, Mr. Trott. It is time somebody taught you some respect!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Sidney Trott
msgid "Ha! Pity nobody taught you how to fight!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You approach a small village. The houses are dilapidated and the villagers "
"look morose and sickly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Greetings, villagers. Pray tell, what ails you my friends?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid ""
"Ah, is it the men of the monastery? Do you come to offer aid or merely to "
"lecture us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "We come to help, of course. But what is the cause of your condition?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid ""
"The village of Trelo is stricken with some sort of plague. We know not why "
"or where this curse has come from, but we have suffered greatly at its mercy."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid ""
"For several moons we have been so afflicted; none of our herbal remedies has "
"availed. I doubt if even you can cure this damned disease."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid ""
"I fear we are doomed. Perhaps you should make haste away, lest the blight "
"affects you also. Yes, best that you leave us to rot in peace. It is over..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Nonsense! We are well versed in the arts of healing. Let us at least try to "
"remedy this ailment."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"On closer inspection the villagers of Trelo seem to be suffering from an "
"unusually strong poison."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Hmm, this illness runs deep indeed. I fear any cure I provide will be short-"
"lived."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid "I knew it! It is hopeless, even the white brothers cannot help us now!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The level of poison in your body baffles me, it is as if you were ingesting "
"the venom daily. Let me think... maybe your well is poisoned?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid ""
"Are you mad? You think we would bring this blight upon ourselves! In any "
"case, We drink from the stream - we have no need of a well. It seems you "
"come to lecture us after all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I mean to do nothing of the sort. "
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Gregi turns away, his eyes glazed over."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Brothers, I believe we should seek out the source of this plague. These "
"peasants may have lost hope, but their lives are not yet gone."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"The stench in this place is almost unbearable. Hang on, what's that "
"splashing I hear?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The floor is covered with debris and slimy piles of organic matter."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The floor is strewn with the foul deposits of the cave creatures."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "There is something glinting amongst this fetid waste..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You delve your hand into the muck and retrieve a dirty silver locket. "
"Opening it you find a small, smudged painting of a young woman."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Hmm. I don't recognise the likeness, but I suppose I should keep hold of "
"this trinket nonetheless."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"The noxious beast is slain. These vulgar creatures are no doubt responsible "
"for the plague in Trelo."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Yes, it would seem that the villagers' water supply has been contaminated by "
"the toxic bodily waste of these ghouls."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "People of Trelo, the curse has been lifted, the plague is over!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The villagers gather around and you explain to them the source of their "
"misfortune."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid ""
"Thank you, my friends. I must apologise for my earlier impudence. I doubted "
"you, but without reason."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gregi
msgid ""
"I should like to reward your efforts, but we are a poor township. I only "
"hope our eternal gratitude is enough..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Goodbye, for now. And may hope never desert you again."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You enter the hovel. It is sparsely furnished and smells of mould. The only "
"thing that is really of interest is a leather sack upon the kitchen table."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Ah, the sack contains gold, around 30 coins. It must be the village funds..."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Take the sack"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"These villagers have no need of such wealth. I shall claim it as my own."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Leave it be"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "This clearly belongs to another, it is not mine for the taking."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You come across a shallow pond. Floating on the surface is a bright white "
"lily. Its petals exude a soft aroma."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Take the lily"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "That flower would make a fitting adornment to my robe, I shall take it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As you reach to pick the flower a bud opens, spraying a thick jet of spores "
"into the air. You are unable to avoid inhaling the swirling vapours."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Leave the lily"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I shall leave the lily as it is, but perhaps first I shall consider it some."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This, I believe, is a Sapphire Tulip. In some places these flowers are used "
"as essential spices in wine-making."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You pick the Tulip and store it safely."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You knock on the door of the mountain shack and it is soon answered by an "
"aged, unkempt man brandishing a mace."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Hermit"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "What do'ya want?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I am from the monastery of light. There is no need to be on your guard."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Well...?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I merely wish to ask you a question..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Huh! Why do you monks bother me? Shouldn't you be up in the mountains "
"praying to your damned tree?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"No, it is our duty to travel forth through the land, bringing light where "
"there is dark."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The hermit cackles, revealing a toothless grin."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You think you can cleanse this land? You think you can stem the evil that "
"flows from the hearts of all creatures? You are fools!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"I am done with the world. It can burn, it can rot. Neither you nor I can "
"save it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Goodbye!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The hermit retreats into his abode, slamming shut the wooden door."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"I guess we should be on our way. Only those whose eyes are open can be "
"guided by the light."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"I suppose, though the hermit's manner hangs heavy upon my heart. I do not "
"believe he is an evil man, just one who is weary."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "That may be so, but for now we must leave him be."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Begone!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I will not let you slink away into your misanthropy, brother. We know who "
"you truly are."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The hermit slowly opens the door."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Of what do you speak?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"There was a time when you were not so damning of life. Was it not so? Were "
"you not once a brother of the light?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Your words anger the old man, suddenly a weary rage flashes across his face. "
"He throws off his rags and reveals himself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Romas
msgid ""
"Yes, I was once a student of Maldor. My name was Romas, but that means "
"little now. I have spent four years trying to forget the events that took "
"place - and now, in your naivety, you come to drag up the past. All I seek "
"for myself is solitude, and it seems I will have to fight to preserve it..."
msgstr ""

#. [spell]: id=scourge
#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "Scourge"
msgstr ""

#. [spell]: id=miracle
#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "Miracle"
msgstr ""

#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "Summon Ogre expired"
msgstr ""

#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "Summon"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Romas
msgid ""
"At least in death I am free from the weight of the past and the terrible "
"burden of morality. Goodbye fools, your day will come too."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As Romas keels over, his hand reaches out to you in one faint, final "
"gesture. Uncurling his fingers you find a small tablet of stone bearing "
"strange etchings."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"This is a spell of some sort - it must be the incantation to gain entrance "
"to the Glimero Caverns! But why would one who made us his enemy leave it to "
"us? A last act of kindness - or of vengeance?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"I do not know. Nor can I say I understand the bitterness that possessed this "
"man. And to think he has lived within earshot of the monastery all this "
"time! It is a sad and mysterious story, but perhaps we will learn more of it "
"in the caverns."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Out the corner of your eye you catch sight of something moving in a small "
"patch of swamp. You look closer and spot a slimy lump of brown matter "
"squirming in the mud."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What on earth is that?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"No name for it comes to my lips, but it is clearly an abomination! Prepare "
"for battle!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Attack the repugnant beast"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Yes, I will the slay the thing, no matter what its origins. A being which "
"offends the senses so wholly should be killed forthwith."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Approach it cautiously"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "No, I will investigate it further."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As you advance, the creature emits a dribbling sound - which grows louder as "
"you near."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Interesting..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Suddenly, the creatures falls silent and two eyes open in the rough, earthy "
"skin. They stare at you imploringly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I do believe this creature is sentient! I would judge by its manner that it "
"is only an infant."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Careful, it might still be dangerous."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Glugg
msgid "Shholpoupl..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Look at it! It is harmless, a mere baby."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Glugg
msgid "Lsshlloupl... Shhhloblm..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Perhaps it is lost, looking for its parents? Why don't we bring it with us, "
"I am rather fond of the creature really."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "If you must. But take care not to soil your fine robes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Glugg
msgid "Shholpoupl! Shhlop! Shhlop!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Glmip-Gup
msgid "Shhlorp! Shhlorp!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Ah, Glugg has found its home at last..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Glugg
msgid "Shhlorp-Gup!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Farewell!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"A mounted elf bursts through the trees. His expression is stern and his "
"steed is fiery."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Elif
msgid "Turn back! The forest does not want you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ryionee
msgid "The hunt begins!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "We mean you no harm, elf!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ryionee
msgid "Then die quietly, traitor!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"All of a sudden, from the trees around you, a party of elven druids emerge..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Falyrlia
msgid "We have been waiting for you, men of the monastery."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Is this a greeting?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Falyrlia
msgid "No, it is your end. You will venture no further!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Suddenly the foliage around you starts moving."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Aha, one of the legendary treemen! A fascinating find indeed..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bairkre
msgid "You dare return! Go now, or forever stay - beneath my roots!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I believe it means to attack me. I have heard much of the peaceful nature of "
"such treefolk - does none of it ring true?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"I have also heard much of the power of their mighty trunks. Flee, unless you "
"wish to test this truth also!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Two elven warriors jump from their hiding place among the treetops. Their "
"weapons are drawn."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Eldro
msgid "Go from here, covetous fools!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The leafless tree is adorned with numerous etchings. There seems to be "
"ancient symbols scratched into the bark."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"It must be the same Paulos wrote of. Maybe there is some magic attached to "
"it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Aye, that seems likely. If I were to make an etching - perhaps something "
"will come of it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "I don't know what this means, and I daren't meddle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "What will you attempt to etch?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A picture of a tree"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch a picture of a tree."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "All of a sudden an arrow slams into your side."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A circle"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch a circle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Just as you finish the etching a huge branch falls from a tree knocking you "
"to the ground."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "An arrow"
msgstr "Uma Flecha"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch an arrow."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You scratch a small arrow into the bark when suddenly a droplet of sticky "
"sap squirts in your face."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A skull"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch a skull."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"After finishing the skull you realise to your horror that one of the trees "
"to your side is looming over you menacingly."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A picture of an antelope"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch a picture of an antelope."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As soon as you finish drawing the antelope, you hear a whistling high above."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A moment later you are hit by a hail of arrows."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A flower"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch a flower."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You scratch a flower into the bark when suddenly a droplet of sticky sap "
"squirts in your face."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A sword"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch a sword."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The moment you finish drawing, there is a commotion in the bushes behind you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You are suddenly surrounded by angry elves."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A mountain"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will etch a mountain."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The moment you finish etching, an arrow slams into the tree - narrowingly "
"missing you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Then another arrow hits you squarely in the back."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I'm not going to risk it."
msgstr ""

#. [effect]
msgid "wand"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Draylia
msgid "Begone, reckless mortals. You have no business here!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"To the contrary, we are here in search of our missing brother, Paulos. We "
"have reason to believe he came this way four years past."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Draylia
msgid ""
"Indeed, and here he remains. Do you not recognise the face of our statue?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Paulos! So you have hold him a prisoner in stone, but why? I had heard the "
"elves were just and fair creatures, not cruel jailers!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Draylia
msgid ""
"Oh but we are. Your brother tried to take what was not his. And now he gazes "
"upon it daily - with eyes of stone. He is now that which he coveted, an "
"object himself. Is this not justice?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Even if his actions were rash his motives were pure. Why refuse the use of "
"your amulet in the first place? Are you impervious to Quaxoir? Or perhaps "
"you are in league with the dreaded one?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Draylia
msgid ""
"I could sense that your brother's heart was full of fear. That is why I "
"refused his request. When he tried to steal the Amulet it confirmed my "
"concern: he was not fit to possess such an artifact."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"And nor are you, wicked woman of the woods! We shall free our brother from "
"your cruel clutches!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Draylia
msgid ""
"Gather to me, elves of Gladerin forest... The time for fighting has again "
"arisen!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Draylia
msgid "My body perishes; my spirit passes. Farewell foolish mortals!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"With the death of the Elven Queen the magic holding Paulos has subsided, "
"though not vanished."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Perhaps now we should attempt to free our brother from his prison of stone? "
"I think I already know the spell..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"The Elven Queen is gone, yet our brother Paulos remains imprisoned. Perhaps "
"we shall yet find a way to free him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid "At last, free from that cursed state!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid ""
"Brothers, I broke the code and paid by imprisonment. Am I offered a chance "
"for redemption?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Paulos, you were wrong to try to prize that precious relic from the bosom of "
"the forest folk. But we were wrong to spill innocent blood in order to "
"rescue you. We should both now seek redemption."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid ""
"Let us flee this forest and pray the gods will heal the hearts of these "
"hapless elves. Will you accompany me to the monastery? Once there, I will "
"begin again. Another four years of study awaits me. Maldor need not know of "
"either of our misdemeanours."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Agreed. We will ensure you reach the monastery in safety."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid ""
"How I longed for death these past years, and now it comes I am full of nowt "
"but horror!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "With Paulos dead we have failed our mission. Forgive us Maldor..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid ""
"Funny. In my youth I strove so hard to renounce the temptations of the "
"flesh, yet now I have known what it is to truly feel nothing I am delighted "
"to return to the realm of the senses. The scent of the trees, the merest "
"breeze - these things now strike me as wonderous beyond reckoning."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid ""
"Ah, it has not changed one bit. These young mages scurry about just as we "
"did before them. The pathos is powerful, my brothers. Thank you and "
"farewell. Where is Maldor? I should go speak with him at once."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"Ah, my young disciple returns! It gladdens me to see that your travels have "
"not dimmed your spark, Paulos."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid ""
"Alas, if only it were so. We have much to discuss, Maldor. I wish to begin "
"my training again, I still have much to learn."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "The Eklin Amulet!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "We have done enough harm to these elves already. Leave it be."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Take the amulet"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The damage is done - what more harm would it do? Besides, to leave it would "
"risk it finding an evil owner..."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Leave it"
msgstr "Deixa-o"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Agreed, I shall leave it to the elves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Paulos
msgid "After all that has passed, I cannot bring myself to take the Amulet."
msgstr ""

#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "-$eklin_damage"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"This seems to be an old tavern, but it is obviously abandoned. Most of the "
"rooms are empty, save for a scattering of kitchen utensils."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Take a meat cleaver"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I'll take this meat cleaver, it might make a decent weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I cannot carry another weapon, I am already too laden."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Take a bucket"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I'll take this bucket, it might be of some use."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The well is missing a bucket and appears to be broken. You peer over the rim "
"but it is too dark to see how deep it goes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Brothers, did I not see one of you carrying a bucket with you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I've got an idea!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You tie your bucket to the end of the rope and lower it into the depths. "
"Once the rope has reached its end, you begin winding it back again."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The bucket is much heavier now, and you have to strain to wind the pulley. "
"When the bucket appears above the rim of the well, you almost fall over in "
"shock: there is someone in it!"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Ruffian, id=Bill
msgid "Bill"
msgstr "Bill"

#. [effect]: type=impact
msgid "ratcatcher"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid "Hello. How do you do? Me name's Bill."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The man climbs out of the bucket, and brushes himself down."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid "Much obliged, by the way. Forever in your debt."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What for?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid "For rescuing me, of course. Heard me shouting for help no doubt."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Well, er..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid ""
"I tell you what, I was at my wits end down there. Dry enough, but boring as "
"hell."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid ""
"Only so many rats you can eat without losing your mind a bit, if you know "
"what I mean."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "How long were you down there for?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid ""
"Oh, a couple of weeks probably. Fell down there after one too many drinks, "
"if you get me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I see."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid "Anyway, what can do for you? Gotta repay the debt, ain't I?"
msgstr ""

#
#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr "O que queres dizer?"

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid "Well, what's your business in these parts?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "As it happens, my companions and I are on a journey of some import."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid ""
"In that case, I will join you. It looks like you could do with a bodyguard, "
"eh?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Okay, Bill. You are welcome to accompany us as long as you wish."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bill
msgid "Right. Which way?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Dammit, I should have stayed down that well."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "These finely crafted statues depict some sort of winged creature."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Phew, the heat in here is intense!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Around the passage the air is hot and smells of smoke."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "This must be Mount Sulphur. Let us proceed with caution."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Suddenly you hear shouting and the roaring of flame."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Brothers, there seems to be a battle ahead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Frannel
msgid ""
"Who comes upon our rear? White mages no less. What business have you here?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "We are from the Brotherhood of Light, seeking to complete our training."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Frannel
msgid ""
"We too seek to complete our training, yet we hail from the Brotherhood of "
"Fire. What is your quest?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "To spread the light and give help to whose in need. What is yours?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Frannel
msgid "We seek to return the sceptre of fire to our master."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Droilx
msgid "Begone, minion of fire!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The clasher lashes out at one of the red mages, striking him with his blade."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Frannel
msgid "Enough talk! We are in need right now, White Brother. Will you help us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Of course - our staffs shall be united. Let there be light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Frannel
#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Let there be fire!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The sceptre of fire is within my grasp! I can sense its energy bristling "
"before me..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Do not be broken by the lure of power, brother. We promised to aid our fiery "
"cousins in retrieving this sceptre, and that we shall do."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Take the sceptre"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Why should they claim this weapon for themselves when I am the one who has "
"risked most to reach it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As you take the sceptre a shower of sparks fly from its glowing red ruby."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I shall wield this weapon! It is mine!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: role=redmage
msgid ""
"Treachery! The monastery of light is nowt but a haven of frauds and thieves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: role=redmage
msgid "Brothers, we must turn on these traitors!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "You are right, I shall leave it for the brothers of fire."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "The sceptre is ours! Our task is complete..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Thank you brothers, we owe much to your brave assistance. How may we repay "
"you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Helping others is all we wish for."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "You are a kind kin, but I cannot leave it at that."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The mage hands you a sack cloth."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Here, take this. Inside are four magical gems, one for each of you. They are "
"called brimstones and if kept upon your person they will serve to warm you "
"against even the most icy chill."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Brimstones"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "+50% resistance to cold attacks"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Thank you, these will be of much benefit I am sure."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I hope you never have call to use them. Anyway, we must now depart and "
"return the sceptre. Let there be no more animosity between the brotherhoods."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "The city of Fokio I believe. A friendly place by all accounts..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Daniel
msgid "Old Harold is in terrible shape these days. Maybe you could help him?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What ails you my friend? Why do you wear such a downturned face?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Harold
msgid ""
"That little bastard Grinn has made me homeless. Put up the rents again he "
"has!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Harold
msgid ""
"There I am working till noon every day just to keep him in fancy clothes, "
"and he has the cheek to turf me out of me own home!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Harold
msgid ""
"Penniless, now - that's what I am. And me health not in too good shape "
"neither."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Yes, I can see - perhaps I can help you. Tell me though, why did he raise "
"the rent?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Harold
msgid ""
"Says it's inflation or some such tosh. He reckons cos he saved us from the "
"orcs he can do what he wants."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Hmm. Maybe I can have a word with him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Harold
msgid ""
"I doubt it'll much good. That boy's a right horror, too much pride in the "
"lad - that's his problem."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Baron Grinn has agreed to lower your rent, you should be fine."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Harold
msgid ""
"What! Really? I dread to think what you did to him to make him change his "
"mind - but perhaps it's best I don't know."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Harold
msgid "Thank you, though. You saved my skin."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Darcus The Shopkeeper"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Greetings, what bring you to these parts? Perhaps you are heading into the "
"winter plaines - I have everything you need for such an expedition. Please "
"come in and browse my wares."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"A finely-dressed youth addresses you. He is polite yet seems somewhat "
"arrogant."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"Hello there! Welcome to Fokio. I am Baron Grinn, judge and ruler of this "
"city. We are pleased to entertain such esteemed company."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "May I help you at all?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "Ask him about Fokio"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What can you tell me about your fine city, sir?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"Ah, yes. Fokio. It is a fine place to live. Situated on the Southwest edge "
"of the Winter Plaines, it has long been a stopping-off point for hunters and "
"other travellers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"Of course, we live in the shadow of Mount Sulphur - but there is little to "
"worry about there. The volcano has been dormant for aeons they say."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I notice you do not seem to have many farmers living here, how do you feed "
"your people?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"Oh, our food mostly comes from the trappers who hunt the beasts of the snow. "
"In fact, I believe there is a hunting party out on the plaines as we speak."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I see, thank you. May your reign here be long and fruitful."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "Ask him if any other mages have been to Fokio"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Have any other mages from the monastery passed through here, perhaps some "
"years ago?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"We have heard much of the monastery, but sightings of your kin are scarce. "
"However, a party of mages did come to Fokio once."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Really? This is good news, tell me more..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"There is not much to tell I'm afraid. They arrived from the West one stormy "
"night, and took lodgings here. I must admit I was a little taken aback by "
"their manner. They seemed preoccupied and kept to themselves. When I awoke "
"they were gone."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"The landlord of the tavern in which they stayed said they left at the crack "
"of dawn, crossing the north-eastern bridge."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Thank you very much Baron Grinn, you have been most helpful."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "Ask him how he became the ruler of Fokio"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "How does one so young become a ruler?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"That is a long tale, my friend. How does one start to recount such a "
"victory, such a daring heroic adventure?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"It all began some years ago, when I was but a poor farmhand and Fokio was "
"under attack from the orcs across the lake..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Before you can interrupt, Baron Grinn begins a well-rehearsed story of how "
"he rescued the township from the clutches of orcish raiders."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Eventually he finishes the yarn with a vivid description of his climactic "
"duel with the orcish king."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"An impressive saga, Baron. And an equally impressive way with words. You "
"would have made a fine bard if warrior were not your calling."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "Thank you, mage."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Baron Grinn
#. [option]: id=Gerridan
msgid "Offer to trade with him"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Do you wish to trade, Baron Grinn?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"Without meaning to be impudent, I very much doubt whether you have the "
"wherewithal to purchase anything I possess. Try Darcus' shop in the centre "
"of town."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "Ask him why he raised Harold's rent"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Baron, I should like to ask you why you saw fit to put up your rents "
"recently?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"With all due respect, you mages have no right to probe Fokio's internal "
"affairs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"One of your farmers is homeless, Baron. He has been made destitute by your "
"constant demands. Why do you pile suffering upon him?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"Listen! That is none of your business! I am the ruler and judge of this "
"city. It was I who liberated these people from the orcish tyranny! If it "
"wasn't for me these people would be slain, or worse driven into slavery "
"beneath the orcish whip!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Very well. I do not admire your sovereignship, but I shall respect it. "
"Farewell, Baron!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"You are mistaken, Baron. Or perhaps, more to the point - you are a liar! I "
"have it on good authority that Fokio came into your hands through gambling."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "How dare you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Please dispense with the airs and graces you have taken to so preciously. "
"Anyone can see you are too young to have fought the orcs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Unless you release your yoke on the people of Fokio I will spread the news "
"far and wide. All will know Baron Grinn is a liar."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid "But..."
msgstr "Mas..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "It is your choice."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Baron Grinn
msgid ""
"Please don't tell anyone about this. I will drop the rent for Harold and the "
"others immediately... just keep it to yourself okay?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Agreed. I will keep my side of the bargain if you keep yours."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Smift
msgid "These damn fields! Will we never pull in the crop?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Ahoy there! What is the name of this place?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jonna
msgid "This is the village of Borol."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Who is in charge here? Does the village have a leader?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jonna
msgid ""
"Indeed, Gerridan is his name. If you're new here you better go speak with "
"him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "That I will do."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid "Greetings. I am Gerridan of Borol."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Greetings, Gerridan. I hail from the monastery of light."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"Do you mind telling me what those goblins are doing on our fields? The "
"townsfolk are up in arms about it!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"You have nothing to fear, Gerridan. They are bringing in your harvest - as a "
"sign of goodwill. Tell your people that they mean no harm."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"They are goblins! We have spent years fighting their kin, and you expect us "
"now to let them walk among us without a qualm?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"All things can be reversed, my friend. The hatred that has grown between you "
"is understandable, but not irrevocable. Besides, these goblins have fled "
"from their orcish rulers. You share a common enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid "That may be so, but how are we to trust them?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Keep them under watch if need be, all that is required from you is a little "
"forebearance. It seems Pocko and his goblins wish to reside in the mountains "
"north of here. Perhaps one day you may regard them as friends."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"If lore did not vouchsafe your wisdom I would deem your words full of folly. "
"But it seems I have no choice in the matter. The goblins may work for us, if "
"they choose - but I will request King Lyodus sends a guard to keep them "
"under watch."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Do as you will, but let not hope be failed by the grudges of the past."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid "Leave the town at once!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid "May I be of assistance?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Gerridan
msgid "Ask him about Borol"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Tell me about this village of yours..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"There is not much to tell I'm afraid. We are a simple farming community "
"under the guardianship of good King Lyodus. We pay him tribute, and he "
"offers us protection. Thanks to him, our affairs have been peaceful of late."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"However, the village has lost many men to the damned orcs in the last few "
"years. Now we lack the hands to even pull in the harvest each summer. I fear "
"a famine may be some way off..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I am sorry to hear that..."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Gerridan
msgid "Ask if he has seen any other white mages"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Gerridan, have any other white mages visited your village in the last few "
"years?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"No, none of your kind has seen fit to pass through here, though there has "
"been numerous occasions when we have wished it so. We hold you in high "
"regard, brothers of the light."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I am sorry if you have received no help from the Brotherhood in these trying "
"times. Our numbers are small and our duties many. I'm sure you understand."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid "Of course. Our troubles here have not been too pressing I suppose."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Of what do you speak, Gerridan?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"Oh it is nothing really. About four years ago, a strange monument appeared "
"in the woods very near here. Though it has brought us no harm, there have "
"been times when all manner of terrible noises have rung out in the night."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"Its frightening aspect has led many locals to believe the place is haunted. "
"I don't believe it myself, but how it came to be is nevertheless a mystery."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Thanks for the information, Gerridan. We shall investigate it further."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "May we trade goods with you sir? We are in need of provisions..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Gerridan
msgid ""
"You are free to use our village to rest, but I'm afraid we have no supplies "
"to offer you. You'd be better off paying a visit to old man Morridon - he's "
"a herbalist. The north road leads to his adode."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Gerridan
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "*No thanks"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid ""
"Excuse me, sir. Have you perchance come across a soldier by the name of Max "
"on your travels?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Um, let me think..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid ""
"Last harvest he set forth southwards, towards the famed training camp of "
"Lord Kaspian."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid ""
"When our father died he left us a small inheritance. Both Max and I longed "
"to train with the great Kaspian so as to join King Lyodus' army - but we had "
"funds only for one. I drew the short straw; so it was my brother who was to "
"be the soldier."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid ""
"Yet, I have not heard word from him since he left. I am concerned he did not "
"find safe passage."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid "Have you seen him?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "No, Bardley, I am afraid not."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Yes - your brother Max is held captive by thieves in the Western Woods. We "
"were unable to rescue him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid ""
"If you cannot free him then no one can! Maybe the story of your order's past "
"deeds were spun upon less than the truth."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid "Do you bring news of my brother?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Yes, he was held captive by the thieves of the Western Wood. But we freed "
"him. He has continued onto Kaspian's training camp."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Bardley
msgid ""
"You bring good news indeed! I am indebted to you sincerely - let there be "
"light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This must be the place Paulos spoke of in his journal. I would surmise that "
"Quaxoir intended it as some sort of portal - perhaps to summon monsters from "
"the other side."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"You speak darkly, my brother. Does the sight of the shrine oppress you so? "
"In any case, it seems to have been abandoned for only faint traces of dark "
"magic linger here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Yes, I sense that too. But I fear that if this portal had ever been used, "
"the world would surely have been flooded by a deluge of chaos. I wonder what "
"happened to hinder Quaxoir's plans."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This is a strange portal of some kind. I know not of its purpose here, yet "
"it seems to emanate an evil sense."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As you approach the house an angry voice calls out from behind the locked "
"door..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Old Man Morridon"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Begone I tell you! I am a magician of great power... Harass me further and I "
"will unleash my magic upon you!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Turn back"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Introduce yourself"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "You have nothing to fear from me old man, I am..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Before you can finish a rock flies from one of the windows striking you "
"squarely on the arm. You take a leap backwards to avoid any further attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Advance towards the front door"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You advance closer to the house when suddenly the door swings open."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Ah, now you come closer I see you are a friend, come in! Sorry about my "
"rather rude greeting, I assumed you were another brown-skinned nuisance..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Brown-skinned nuisance?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Oh, a bunch of goblins has been bothering me these last few days. Keep "
"shouting off outside my window for some reason. Mind you, it's nothing that "
"a well-aimed good rock can't solve."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "What of the great magic you spoke?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The old man smiles mischievously."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Well, there's nothing that a bit of bragging can't solve neither. Most of me "
"magic is herbal you see, them goblins aren't scared of that sort. The rock "
"does the trick though."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Where do the goblins come from?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Beats me. Started pestering me a couple of days ago. Always hollering "
"outside my window they are. Bloody nuisance."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Maybe we could deal with this matter..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"That'd be nice. Tell you what - you get rid of the goblins and I'll cook you "
"up some nice magic brews. Sound fair?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=units
msgid "The goblins are dead. They will trouble you no longer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Heavens and blessings! Thank you so much..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Finally some peace for the old man! Here, have this in return for your "
"efforts..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Dharma Potion: +4 Max Mana"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Drop by whenever you wish, I should be able to sell you some more little "
"treats."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You again? I heard how you tried to pander to that dirty bunch of goblins on "
"the expense of the townsfolk. Good thing Gerridan had more sense than you. "
"Now get lost, you'll get nothing from me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The old man slams the door shut."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid "Huh? Who's that?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "The Brotherhood of Light. We come to rid the land of your foul stench!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid "Come on then! Me goblins will have you!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Attack the goblins"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Talk to them"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The Brotherhood of Light. Lay down your spears, we do not come to fight."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr "Huh?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Why do you pester the old man so?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid ""
"The rock man? We keeps trying to talk to him. See - we escaped from the orc "
"lands over lake. Zanaibar is a bastard, we don't want him as king no more. "
"Always picking on us goblins."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "So you have deserted the orcish army? But why come here?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid ""
"Dunno, hoping humies might let us stay up here. Not done no wrong. Just need "
"a bit of food that's all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid ""
"We tried asking the rock man for help, but we can't eat rocks. He is bastard "
"too."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"He thought you meant to injure him. He did not understand you were seeking "
"help..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Sadly many will think the same. Your kind is both feared and hated on these "
"shores. It is best that you return..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid ""
"If we go back, we die. Zanaibar will kill us surely. If we stay however..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Pocko smirks to the other goblins and they raise their spears."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid "...it is you that will die!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"If it is true that you seek to live in peace on these shores, then maybe "
"there is a solution..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid "Yes, that's what we seek! Peace."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The village of Borol is not far from here. Due to the wars with your kin "
"they lack the manpower to gather their harvest. Perhaps if you repaid the "
"debt, the folk here would let you remain..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid "You think the humies would let us stay? Do you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"If the hearts of men are true, then forgiveness will follow. I can only hope "
"the people of Borol are not blinded by their grievances - however justified "
"they may be."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Begin at once on the farm, and I will pray that tolerance will prevail."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Pocko
msgid "Right. Move out, lads."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Demand they board their ship and leave"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Return at once to whence you came, vile vermin! This land is no home to "
"you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kiollot
msgid "Hello there!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Hello - what is this place?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kiollot
msgid ""
"You are approaching Kaspian's training camp. He's in his office if you want "
"to speak to him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid ""
"Hello and welcome to my training camp. I am Kaspian - expert in weapons, "
"master of combat."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid ""
"This land is a dangerous place don't you think? You won't last long these "
"days without a sturdy sword-arm or a steady aim. Here at the camp I can help "
"you fulfil your true potential as a fighter."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid ""
"For only 200 gold you'll be coached in various fighting techniques by two "
"true veterans of battle, Claude and Sibblos. Access to our specialist "
"armoury is also included in the price. Since you men of the monastery are "
"such a rare sight around here, I'll even let you all train here for the "
"price of one!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid "Only you can defend yourself, but only I can teach you how!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid "So, do you want to enroll?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Kaspian
msgid "Yes, sign us up"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Sign us up."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid "Good move, friend. Hopefully it'll be the first of many."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Kaspian takes your money, counts it and gets you to sign your names on a "
"scroll."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid ""
"Right, you may use the camp at your leisure. You have paid for a total of "
"four full sessions, it is up to you and your comrades how to use them. Go "
"see Claude and Sibblos to begin your training. You are also allowed to shop "
"at our armoury from now on, even after you've finished your training."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kaspian
msgid ""
"You don't have enough gold. Stop wasting my time. Come back when you can "
"afford it!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Kaspian
msgid "No thanks, maybe later"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Claude
msgid ""
"Please leave the training arena - you must enroll before I can begin "
"teaching you. If you want to sign up, go and see Kaspian."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Claude
msgid ""
"Hi, my name is Claude. I specialise in melee fighting, up close and deadly. "
"Are you ready? Which technique shall we start with?"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
#. [option]: id=Claude
msgid "Mighty Blow"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Claude teaches you how to take advantage of an opponent's weak points, "
"demonstrating various methods to maximise the impact of your weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "<span color='green'><big>+1 damage to all melee weapons</big></span>"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
msgid "(+1 damage to all melee weapons)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Claude
msgid "Your training is complete now - you have done well. Good luck to you."
msgstr ""

#. [command]
#. [option]: id=Claude
msgid "Defensive Stance"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Claude demonstrates how to use controlled moves to retain balance whilst "
"fighting. This technique allows you to swing your weapon easier and faster."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "<span color='green'>+1 strikes to all melee weapons</span>"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
msgid "(+1 strikes to all melee weapons)"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
#. [option]: id=Claude
msgid "Attack of Opportunity"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Claude teaches you to read your opponent and see where their focus is "
"directed, allowing you to strike at the right moment to catch them off-guard."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<span color='green'>You receive +10% chance to hit against enemies adjacent "
"to an ally when using a non-magical attack.</span>"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
msgid ""
"(+10% chance to hit with non-magical attacks against enemies adjacent to an "
"ally)"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Claude
msgid "No, I'm not ready to start yet. But I'll be back."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Sibblos
msgid ""
"Please leave the shooting range at once! You have to enroll before you are "
"allowed in here. Speak to Kaspian, he will deal with you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Sibblos
msgid ""
"Greeting, Sibblos is my name. I can teach you everything you need to know "
"about the art of ranged combat. Except of course, these magical weapons of "
"yours - they are outside of my expertise. What do you want me to teach you?"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
#. [option]: id=Sibblos
msgid "Accuracy"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Sibblos gives you advice on steadying your nerves and teaches you to "
"instinctively aim for the most vulnerable parts of the body. After much "
"practise you seem to be hitting the target almost every time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<span color='green'><big>+1 damage to all non-magical ranged weapons</big></"
"span>"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
msgid "(+1 damage to all non-magical ranged weapons)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Sibblos
msgid ""
"You have made a great deal of improvement, my friend. But your training is "
"now over."
msgstr ""

#. [command]
#. [option]: id=Sibblos
msgid "Rapid Fire"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Sibblos shows you how best to handle your weapon. Eventually you grasp the "
"technique and find you are able to shoot at a much higher rate."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<span color='green'><big>+1 strikes to all non-magical ranged weapons</big></"
"span>"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
msgid "(+1 strikes to all non-magical ranged weapons)"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
#. [option]: id=Sibblos
msgid "Steady"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Sibblos instructs you on how to make best use of your current position and "
"prepare yourself for a quick volley of attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<span color='green'><big>You may attack twice per turn with non-magical "
"ranged weapons, provided that you do not move at all</big></span>"
msgstr ""

#. [command]
msgid ""
"(1 extra attack per turn with non-magical ranged weapons when not moving)"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Sibblos
msgid "Nothing, I'm not ready yet."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You knock on the door of the cottage, but no one answers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Hello?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"You decide to enter anyway, proceeding cautiously. The walls of the cottage "
"are stacked high with books and scrolls."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Unable to resist a quick browse you scan the bookshelves..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "There are some impressive tomes here, it is a fine collection."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Angus"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"I'm glad you find my papers of interest. There is, of course, a lot here of "
"no merit, yet one must sift the sand to find the gems, don't you agree?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Er, yes. Hello. I knocked on the door, but there was no reply..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Seemingly oblivious to your words, Angus moves to one of the bookcases and "
"pulls out a old leather book."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"This one, for instance, I found in amongst a box of terrible dwarven novels. "
"It is quite a find."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Oh? What is the name of the book?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Angus either does not hear you or is too engrossed in his read to notice."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Angus, Dionne from the library says you mentioned something about a mage's "
"journal. We would very much like to see it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Oh, yes! The journal of the headstrong monk, that is another rare beauty. It "
"came into my hands quite by chance..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"It was last summer I think, or was it the one before? Either way, I was "
"walking in the woods north of here when I chanced upon an old abandoned "
"homestead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"That is where I found the journal, hidden beneath a pile of leaves and "
"debris. The origins of the text remain a mystery to me however."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Perhaps if you showed it to us, we may be able to shed some light on the "
"matter..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Angus pulls out a loosely-bound bundle of parchments and hands it to you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Great glory my friends! This is the story of our brother, Paulos!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"There are some blurred passages, but it seems to relate the detail of his "
"journey since he left the monastery four years ago."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Most of the journal is of a studious nature - philosophical musings and "
"notes on various plant-species. But there is a passage here that is most "
"enlightening..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Paulos' Journal"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"After bidding farewell to King Lyodus we travelled northeast, not knowing "
"what further perils this land held in store. Ultar, in particular, was "
"somewhat shaken by what had transpired. Though our recent experiences had "
"left us in no doubt as to the fragile state of peace in the world outside "
"the monastery, none of it had prepared us for what was to come."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Just east of Lake Jesaro we came upon what seemed a half-built village. "
"Indeed, so it must have appeared to any who saw it, at least in the light of "
"day. Believing it to be deserted, we took shelter there for the night."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Romas was the first to wake - just after midnight. Although by day the place "
"was empty, by night it was as noisy as a market town. Thankfully we were "
"hidden amongst the foliage - for when we eyed what was about us our blood "
"fell to a chill."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"An army of frightful creatures laboured through the night, seemingly "
"constructing some kind of shrine - or perhaps a gateway to an underground "
"realm. I could not fathom the purpose of the edifice, yet we all understood "
"well enough what it signified. Our fears were confirmed upon overhearing "
"some of the workers speak the name of the accursed one, Quaxoir."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"There in the bushes we hid, throughout the night, in dismal terror. As "
"daybreak beckoned the undead went below ground, leaving the place eerily "
"silent. When the sun finally rose, we dared to leave our makeshift hiding "
"place and fled with great haste. We spent the next night in Fokio city, "
"before crossing the eastern bridge and heading south into the Gladerin "
"Woods. It was my aim to seek help from the elves rumoured to reside there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"There are pages missing here. We should seek the house wherein Angus found "
"this, perhaps they are still there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "It was north of here, that's all I can remember."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Thank you Angus, you have been most helpful."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"This house has long been deserted. It looks empty, save for the rubbish and "
"debris about the floor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "This must be the house Angus mentioned. Let us search it high and low."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Within half an hour you turn up several pages of manuscript, scattered "
"amongst the rubbish on the floor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Perfect! Let's read what fate befell Paulos next..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"We have taken lodgings in an unused abode in the woods. In the morn I shall "
"seek out the tree of symbols in Gladerin Forest and relate our story to the "
"elves. If all goes well they will grant me possession of their famed relic, "
"The Eklin Amulet. It will be a decisive weapon in the coming battle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Curse those elves! My meeting proved fruitless due to the damned "
"indifference of the forest-folk. Can they not see that they too are in "
"danger should Quaxoir's evil spread across the land? In any case, I have "
"resolved to steal the amulet this very night. The amulet's magic is too "
"valuable an ally to let it go."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"When I discussed my plan with the others Ultar fell into a mighty temper. He "
"held forth with utmost piety, accusing me of dreadful iniquity. I could not "
"stand Ultar's incessant sermonising - it felt like we were still in the "
"temple back at the monastery. The outside world, I have learnt, often forces "
"one onto a more pragmatic path."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"I am sorry to say that heated words were exchanged today. Ultar left "
"immediately, persuading Romas to travel with him to confront Quaxoir in "
"person. Much as I respect Ultar's courage, I doubt his chances. I stayed "
"behind, alone. Tonight I will slip into the elven castle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"That's where it ends! Not the most cheering of tales, but at least it gives "
"us some clues..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Strange, though the foliage here looks tropical, there is a harsh icy wind "
"coming from the south."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This is most peculiar. Ice on a beach? A moment ago my robes were soaking my "
"sweat, now they cling to me sodden in the face of this cold south-eastern "
"wind."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Brother Trullo
msgid ""
"Life is a misfortune built on pain,\n"
"So let the living by the dead now be slain."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This tome bristles with the chill of dark magic. It must be the means by "
"which they raised those monsters from the dead..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Indeed, and we should dispose of it without delay - its nefarious magic "
"should never be drawn on again."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I daren't even touch the cursed volume!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Throw the book into the sea"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You toss the tome over the edge into the sea."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Forever shall it lay beyond the reach of those who might be tempted by its "
"dark lure."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Study the spell"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"We should not refuse what has been given to us! This spell, though dark in "
"origin, can surely be put to the purpose of light. I shall study the "
"incantation..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This looks like a letter. Indeed, it is addressed to the fortress' wicked "
"sorcerers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Brothers Of Ice,\n"
"\n"
"I know we have worked together in the past to great reward. Are our "
"sympathies still as one? I believe the monastery of light has sent forth "
"another four fools. I doubt I shall be much hindered by their interference, "
"yet I deem it wise to prepare for their arrival. Will the brotherhood of ice "
"come to my aid once more? Please travel to my palace - if need be you may "
"leave your young sorcerers behind to defend the fortress.\n"
"\n"
"- Quaxoir"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I have heard these swamps are home to a curious species of lizard-like "
"creature. I doubt they are the most hospitable of guests..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "This looks like a gravestone, the rock bears an inscription..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Here lies King Reulot. His riches were equalled only by his pride and folly."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Leave it alone"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Let the king rest in peace."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Try to topple the rock"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I want to see what is under this monument..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"With great effort you manage to topple the rock. Beneath it is a crypt, "
"bellowing mist."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The mist gradually assumes a humanoid form. It's cloaked face bears a "
"harrowing expression of regret."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As the spectre perishes, a frail human voice seems to call out from a far-"
"distant realm."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "I do believe we have laid this tormented spirit to rest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Your leg hits something hard just below the surface of the swamp water."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Aha...!"
msgstr ""

#
#. [effect]: type=impact
msgid "net"
msgstr "rede"

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Hello there! What brings men such as these to the Winter Plaines?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "We are merely passing through. Do you mean to waylay us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Of course not, we mean you no harm. Though waylay you we could, if you so "
"choose."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"We are to embark on a hunt. Our game is no mere boar, mind you, but the "
"yeti. It will be dangerous to say the least. Though we have many a bow, we "
"do not have a healer..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Would you care to join us? You will be rewarded handsomely. The meat and fur "
"of a yeti has been known to sell for as high as 800 gold in Fokio city."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Decline the offer"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I have more pressing matters to attend to, Stuart. Thus I must decline your "
"offer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Nevermind, it is your loss. Farewell then!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Stuart gives a blast on his horn and his party set off into the wilderness."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Reprimand the hunters"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I do not agree with the slaughter of such beasts. One must question the "
"humanity of any who murders to merely line their pockets."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Ha! I should have known you would be the pious sort. Your fine feelings have "
"no place here, mage. Come on lads, we should tally no longer. Let the hunt "
"begin!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I fear for the life of this creature. Do you think we should seek it out and "
"give it warning?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Agree to join the hunt"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Yes, we should like to accompany you on your expedition. Lead the way!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Great. We shall leave at once. Let the hunt begin!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Stuart gives a blast on his horn and his party prepare to set off into the "
"wilderness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"The Yeti seems reluctant to leave the winter plaines. It turns and heads "
"back towards the snow-capped mountains."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "The hunt is not over for me yet! I must return to the plaines..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I shan't give up just yet, let me return to the hunt."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "There it is! We've found the yeti!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Ready your weapons boys! Let's bring it down!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The yeti growls, towering above you menancingly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"We mean you no harm, creature of the snow. But there are others who seek to "
"slay you. We come to warn you, that is all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Do you think it understands us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I'm not sure. Perhaps I will cast some healing magic on it as a sign of "
"goodwill."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Once the healing is cast, the beast backs down and seems to give you a "
"quizzical stare."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Suddenly, there is a commotion among the trees."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "So you found it first, eh? We'll take it from here thank you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Never! This creature has done you no harm, we shan't let you slay it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"I'm afraid you are the least of our problems. Stand aside or we'll kill you "
"also."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "So be it. Brothers, prepare for battle!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Lads, use the poison arrows - and shoot to kill. Looks like we're gonna hunt "
"some mages."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Stuart manages to dodge the yeti's attack, reeling back into safety."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Argh, I cannot fight this out any longer. I must flee - I am sorry. Find me "
"in Fokio when it is over. Good luck!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Stuart limps away from the battle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Damn you! Looks like my hunting days are over..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The ground shakes as the yeti's lifeless hulk slams to the ground."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: role=hunter
msgid "It is slain! Let's cut it up and get it back to town."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Thanks for your help, guys. Come see me in Fokio for your reward."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Let's go see Stuart in Fokio City for our reward."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Murderers! There is no redemption for your kind!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Well hello again. It was a fine hunt, don't you think?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "I managed to fetch around 700 gold for that yeti, all told."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Here you go, you and your brothers earned a total of 480g. Nice working with "
"you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Hello again. Sorry I had to bail out of that one, the bugger nearly had me. "
"Might be a while until I go a-hunting again now sadly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Anyway, I managed to fetch around 800 gold for that yeti, all told."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid ""
"Here you go, you and your brothers earned a total of 560g. Nice working with "
"you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "Did you finish the job?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "No, the Yeti still lives."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Stuart
msgid "I'm afraid there is no reward until we bring in the carcass."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Behold, a fallen yeti!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Alas, it looks like it has died of natural causes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: role=hunter
msgid ""
"It also looks like it is on the point of decay. By the time we get it back "
"to Fokio it will have rotted truly. I guess it might be safe to snack upon "
"it now, however. It will give us the strength to fight a living yeti - if we "
"ever find one."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Bury it"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I will bury the poor creature..."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Eat it"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "There is no point letting the thing go to waste. Let's tuck in..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You hack off a piece of yeti flesh and cook it up with some herbs."
msgstr ""

#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "+3 Max HP"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Urgh, most unpleasant. I fear the meat has finally gone off."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "*Leave it be"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid "Who goes there?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "A mage from the monastery of light. Surely you mean us no harm?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid ""
"No, of course not. My wits are weak, that is all. King Lyodus has sent me to "
"deal with the criminals of the Western Woods. They have become bolder over "
"time and he is worried they might turn their greedy eyes towards his castle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"He has sent you on this errand alone? Either he is a cruel king or you are a "
"mighty swordsman indeed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid ""
"Neither, I'm afraid. Though I am loyal to Lyodus, I have not much of a taste "
"for blood. When he rounded up his men to attack the orcs over the lake, I "
"shamefully went into hiding. His scout soon found me, however, and the king "
"threatened to throw me into gaol. As an act of mercy he offered me this "
"endeavour as a means to restore my honour."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"I do not envy you, Godfrey. It seems the king has sent you to your death. "
"However, if perhaps we gave you a little assistance in this task, the king "
"need never know."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid ""
"Would you do that? I would be eternally in your debt. I am to slay a certain "
"criminal named Dillon - once I have done that I can return to the castle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Dillon, you say? I believe we have already slain such a criminal."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid ""
"Damn! Now my honour can never be won back! I shall return empty-handed, and "
"face the gaols..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Godfrey turns, ashen faced, and heads north."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Hang on..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"No, let him go. I sense something noble in Godfrey's willingness to face his "
"fate. Perhaps a greater mercy shall yet prevail."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Let us go flush the forests."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Curse our impatience! We have prevented Godfrey from claiming the prize he "
"held highest, his honour."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid ""
"King Lyodus will be pleased with me at last - I must return at once to the "
"castle and relate the news of my bravery!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid "I return, King Lyodus, my quest complete. Dillon lies dead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Well done Godfrey. I am glad to have put an end to those troublesome "
"thieves, but equally I am pleased you have been able to prove yourself a "
"worthy soldier."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Your task was a tough one, so your reward shall match the deed. I hereby "
"promote you to second-in-command of the castle guard. Arise sir Godfrey!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid "Have you done that which I requested?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid "No, my king. I have not."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Lyodus
msgid ""
"Then be off with you! And do not return until you have fought and killed the "
"one called Dillon."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Godfrey
msgid "Argg! This is why I knew battle was not for me! Goodbye..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Dillon
msgid "Damn mages! Back to your hideaway in the hills!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A hagged man cries out from the cage..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Max
msgid "Can it be true! The Brothers of light are to rescue me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "A sallow looking elf, crouched in his cell, calls out to you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Rilly
msgid "Free me, old man, for the sake of good grace!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Unlock the cage"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You unlock the cage but the key snaps off in your hand..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Rilly
msgid "Praise be with you, I thank my rescuers!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Max
msgid "I am free! Thank you, oh wise men!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The chest contains an old rusty key."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You count the coins, there is 88 gold all told."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I wonder from whom these thieves acquired such a stash?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "This appears to be a treasure map. The paper is worn and brittle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Interesting... there is an 'X' marked upon the page, pointing to an island "
"in the middle of lake Jesaro."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "The map disintegrates in your hand."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Rilly
msgid ""
"I must confess, though I am grateful for my release, I cannot trust you as I "
"would like. Your kind has wronged my queen, and thus I am forced to offer "
"you no friendship."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"We understand, Rilly. We also wish to repent for the damage done to your "
"kind. Hopefully in freeing you we have made some small move towards "
"reconciliation..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Rilly
msgid ""
"It is a noble gesture, yet I'm afraid it is but a feather upon the scales. "
"Nevertheless, I will leave you this as a token of gratitude."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Rilly runs and vanishes into the woods, leaving behind his bow on the stone "
"floor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "What is the cause of this animosity? We have not crossed your queen!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Rilly
msgid ""
"Ah, but another from your monastery has done so. It took place some years "
"ago, but the memory of that misdeed still makes a heavy impression upon my "
"kin."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"So you know of our lost brother perhaps? We have been sent to find those who "
"set forth before us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Rilly
msgid ""
"If you wish to plead your cause with my queen Draylia, you should seek out "
"the Elven Palace. It lies on the far side of your monastery, in the Gladerin "
"Forest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Rilly
msgid ""
"That's all I the help my conscience is willing to impart. Except, beware of "
"the queen's wicked wand! Goodbye."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Rilly runs and vanishes into the woods."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Tell me Max, how did you come to be caged in such a manner?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Max
msgid ""
"I hail from the township of Borol. I was making my way to Kaspian's training "
"camp in the southern glade of the Western Wood, when these damn thieves set "
"upon me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Max
msgid ""
"Believing me to be of higher standing than I am, they kept me under lock and "
"key - hoping one day to hold me to ransom. Alas, the only kin I have is a "
"poor farmer in Borol, my brother."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"We will gladly accompany you to the training camp. These thieves have rotten "
"souls."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Max
msgid ""
"Thank you once more. I can now begin my training - and hopefully one day "
"join the army of King Lyodus..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Good luck, Max."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This must be the spot marked on the map. Let us use our staffs to dig deep "
"into the sand!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "After an hours digging you unearth a wooden chest..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Aha! So this treasure hunt has not been fruitless!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"As you lift the treasure from the chest, two small lizards escape from a "
"concealed compartment."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"They dash towards the water and, in a flurry of splashing, grow in size."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What to make of this commotion - some kind of trap?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Naguard
msgid "Those who claim the gold must also face the guardian!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"This must be the famed Hayshore Market. Let us not tally too long, tis not a "
"place becoming of men of sanctity."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Hellur The Mystic"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Greetings, wise men. I am Hellur, purveyor of magical charms and oddities. "
"Please feel free to browse..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Grundy the Blacksmith"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Hello there. So, even mages are in need armour these days, eh? I'm sure we "
"got something in your size..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Yoll The Chef"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Welcome to my tavern, travellers. It is not often I entertain such esteemed "
"patrons..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Crilk The Mercenary"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Hello, I am Crilk. Need a bodyguard? An assassin? My men will fight to the "
"death for you, providing you carry enough gold..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Talena The Fortune Teller"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Welcome to my grotto, men of the monastery, I have been awaiting your "
"arrival. I am Talena, seer of the not-yet, teller of the to-be."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What is it you do exactly, Talena?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Those in trouble or in need of guidance, come to me, as you do now. For 4 "
"gold pieces I will pass the advice of providence onto you. I am able to sift "
"the sands of time."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
msgid ""
"Consider the lily, but do not pick,\n"
"Beauty upon you may play a trick."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
msgid ""
"The sickness that turns their pallor green,\n"
"May sometimes flow from a source upstream."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
msgid ""
"That which leads you to roam,\n"
"Is often found close to home."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
msgid ""
"There are some beasts built from bone,\n"
"Whose only end is found in stone."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
msgid ""
"Be wary of those who brag and boast,\n"
"Their bravery is often less than most."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
msgid ""
"He who now dwells in despair,\n"
"May once have lived a life of prayer."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
msgid ""
"The torch of leaping fire is found,\n"
"Where molten rock flows underground."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Do you wish to know your fortune for 4 gold pieces?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Talena throws a handful of greenish sand upon a marble slab and begins to "
"trace patterns with her finger. After a few minutes she suddenly looks up "
"and speaks in an ominous drawl..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "I cannot see anything more. Fate only reveals itself so many times."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You have not the funds to furnish my palm. Return when you do."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Ask her to repeat previous fortunes"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "You wish me to reminisce what I have seen so far? Very well..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Suddenly a young person, obviously in a hurry, runs out from behind a house "
"and bumps into you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Oliver
msgid "Beg my pardon - must dash."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Without further ado, the urchin scuttles off down an alleyway. Only later do "
"you realise you have been pickpocketed! The thief has stolen all your gold!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Without further ado, the urchin scuttles off down an alleyway. Only later do "
"you realise you have been pickpocketed! The thief has stolen 30 gold pieces!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid "Yes? I am a very busy man."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid "Ask him about Hayshore Market"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I would like to know a little about your marvellous city, Mayor Jolleson."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"Are you an idiot? This is only Hayshore Market - the most prosperous port on "
"the southern coast. We trade mainly in herbs and spices to and from the "
"scattered islands."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "I see. Tell me, has Hayshore always been so bustling?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"Since the slump ended nearly half a decade ago, yes. Trade has dipped "
"recently, I don't know why, but at least it's not as bad as before."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "May I ask what caused the slump of which you speak?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"External factors of course. Our traders were not to blame, though a number "
"of vessels were lost in a series of freak storms. Others were beset by "
"strange beasts from the deep. Some believe it was related to the business in "
"the Glimero Caverns. I thought all that was over, but rumours have started "
"suggesting similiar occurances in the last few weeks. I remain skeptical, "
"you understand."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "The Glimero Caverns? What transpired there?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"The caverns lie to the west of Hayshore. Now I come to think of it the "
"trouble ended shortly after two mages ventured there. Only one returned, if "
"I recall correctly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What happened to the mage who returned?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"Um, let me think. I don't believe I spoke to him - nobody did. He returned "
"ashen faced and headed north. Anyway, like I said I am busy man."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"That is strange. If he headed north, the road would have taken him back into "
"the mountains. Thank you for your time, Mayor Jolleson."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Perhaps we should head north again, or shall we set off west to investigate "
"these Glimero Caverns?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid "Ask him if any other white mages have been to Hayshore Market"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid "This city has many visitors. How am I to remember them all?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid "Enquire about recent news"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "What has been happening around here of late?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"What is it to you? If you must know, exports are down this month and I am "
"not happy. On top of that I lost a whole company of guards on a vainglorious "
"errand to flush out a terrible beast in the northern foothills... it was a "
"farce. Useless idiots!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "You may be interested to know that we have slain the spider."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"Ha! Am I to believe you killed the beast when a company of my finest have "
"fallen? Stop wasting my time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Perhaps we could help you in some way?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"If you really think a mere mage is a match for that venemous devil, then go "
"ahead. That spider has killed many. I suppose I should reward you if you "
"somehow avoided a likewise fate."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid "Tell the mayor about the spider"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"We have returned, Mayor Jolleson. And the spider is slain. It seems you "
"underestimated us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"Do you expect me to believe this fable? That spider crushes all it sees. You "
"have been nowhere near its lair."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The spider was indeed a menacing foe, but slain it is. Look out beyond the "
"walls of Hayshore, its corpse can be seen still."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"My! You speak the truth... You are braver than I thought. Thank you and "
"farewell, men of the light."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"One moment, Mayor. Though it is not in our nature to chase wealth, you did "
"promise a reward for slaying the spider. I wish to hold you to your word - "
"if only to teach you something of the transience of gold."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Mayor Jolleson
msgid ""
"Huh! Very well, here is a bag of 60 gold pieces. It is all I have upon my "
"person at the present time. Now be on your way, oh pious one."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Farewell. It seems even gratitude is too costly for this blinded soul."
msgstr ""

#
#. [effect]: type=cold
msgid "chill tempest"
msgstr "tempestade gelada"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"This rune emanates a faint magic aura. Perhaps some form of portal, or door? "
"I believe it may be activated, provided we know the correct incantation."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "It seems the portal does not work in reverse."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"If what Mayor Jolleson said is correct, then one of our brothers returned "
"from this place. If we find them we may also learn the incantation - I don't "
"fancy finding out what happens if you get it wrong."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"I don't know the incantation - and I don't fancy finding out what happens if "
"you get it wrong."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Utter the incantation"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Gloiud asdic muloom, kradiret!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "I believe there is someone obstructing the other end of the portal."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"The air in these caverns hang heavy with the latent charge of evil magic. "
"Our mana will be sapped merely being here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"This creature is protected by a powerful icy aura. Our weapons are useless "
"against it! Perhaps only heat can melt the dark chill."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"These dwarven bodies seem limpid and lifeless, yet they do not decompose. "
"This bodes ill."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Quaxoir
msgid "Greetings brothers. I'm glad you could make it... at last."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Why do you speak with such a gloating tongue, Quaxoir? We come to lay you to "
"rest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Quaxoir
msgid ""
"As did the others... If you must know, I have been waiting for you. The "
"brotherhood, paltry as it is, presents the only obstacle on the path to the "
"dark age to be. By coming to me, I have been saved the effort of seeking you "
"out."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Quaxoir
msgid ""
"And for the sake of a fair fight I have invited your counterparts from the "
"brotherhood of ice. I do hope you get along."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"We are not here to contend with your glib threats. You are a blight on this "
"land - we come to rid the world of you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Quaxoir
msgid "Let there be darkness!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "I will not attack a brother!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Quaxoir
msgid ""
"You think you have slain me? I have gone this way before - it means nothing "
"now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid ""
"Saviours! You deliver me from a fate of nightmares! But what brings you to "
"such a place?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"We came to find you, for Maldor. But what treachery led you to side with the "
"dreaded one?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid ""
"Please forgive the actions of one who had no power over them. I was held in "
"the yoke of Quaxoir's magic. It both sustained me in its evil bondage and "
"made me servant to his rancourous will."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid ""
"When the dwarven miners chanced upon this place they unwittingly released "
"Quaxoir from his state of imprisonment. They too met a sorry end."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Yes, we have seen what remains of them. But tell me, how did this tragedy "
"come to pass? Why was Romas able to escape when you remained bound by this "
"unatural servitude?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid "You know of Romas?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Ultar's form begins to fade, as if his soul were passing over ahead of "
"death..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid ""
"Ah... I have suffered much, brothers, and my strength is spent. Listen "
"well..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid ""
"We were foolish to come here at all, Romas and I. Though I fear he followed "
"me only on account of my persuasive rhetoric. You see, my eagerness to "
"impress Maldor was such that I blocked the light of reason from my mind. "
"What else would lead a lowly mage to confront one so versed in the dark "
"paths of black magic?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid ""
"We were no match for Quaxoir, yet luck shone in our favour. After a bitter "
"duel our moment came. And Romas seized it. He had to - even though it meant "
"my demise. An ebb in Quaxoir's powers allowed Romas to cast a stasis field "
"around the wretched wizard. Sadly, I too was caught inside the spell. Romas "
"knew that would be so, but he did the deed nonetheless. The years I spent "
"imprisoned alongside Quaxoir wore down my defenses until I was nothing but "
"his willing slave."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid ""
"Our meeting with Romas was not a happy one. He seemed burdened by a great "
"weight, as if his guilt had all eclipsed the light in his heart. He was a "
"beaten, bitter man by the end."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid ""
"This saddens me gravely, brothers. I do not blame Romas for what he did. "
"That my suffering should be matched by his is not a fate I would have wished "
"for. His act was a noble one, he needn't have punished himself so."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Ultar all but vanishes into the ether of the otherworld."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Ultar
msgid "Farewell brothers. Let there be light!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Forgive me, I have failed you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Fight on my brothers!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Remember me, my friends."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Avenge me, comrades!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<span color='#8888FF'><big>You have proven yourself a worthy leader. (+10 "
"XP)</big></span>"
msgstr ""

#. [unstore_unit]
msgid "+10 XP"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid ""
"Maldor, we have returned. The fate of the four lost brothers is known to us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"Maldor looks on sternly as you explain all that has happened to you since "
"leaving the monastery."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid "It is a sad tale. It seems the four were not what I had hoped."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
msgid "Though some wandered from it, they each trod a noble path, Maldor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"Yes, that is so. But brothers, I have something further to tell you now. "
"When I built this monastery I had a premonition of a moment such as this. I "
"believe you have fulfilled that vision..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"It came to me that four mages from the brotherhood would avail gallantly "
"against the troubles and strife of the outside world. For a long time I "
"deemed it a mere fantasy, but hope grew gradually that the four would emerge."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"This was why I asked you to find Paulos, Ultar, Romas and Goilop. I was "
"convinced they were to be the four...the four that would usher in the new "
"era. It seems that I was mistaken. It is you and your brothers who are the "
"chosen ones."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid ""
"Consider your training complete. Not only have you carried the light of the "
"brotherhood throughout the land, you have caused that light to shine "
"brighter than ever before. My task in founding this brotherhood is complete. "
"From this day henceforth the darkness shall be banished!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid "And so began the age of enlightenment..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Maldor
msgid "Now I go to the light eternal... farewell!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
msgid "Maldor's death means doom for us all."
msgstr ""

