#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Magic"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<big>I.</big>\n"
"This scenario includes a magic system which allows your mages to cast "
"spells. Each spell drains a certain number of mana points - and each player "
"has an individual mana level which gradually replenishes each turn.\n"
"\n"
"By default, each player begins with a maximum mana level of 20 points, and a "
"recovery rate of 2 point per turn. The maximum mana level increases with "
"each levelup, and certain items can raise it as well as the recovery rate. "
"Also, when resting (not attacking nor moving for a turn) you regain 1 point "
"per each movement point instead, meaning that you can recover your mana very "
"quickly by standing still for a few turns.\n"
"<big>II.</big>\n"
"To cast a spell right-click on your mage, choose 'Cast Spell' and a spell "
"menu will appear. Magic upgrades and new spells will be found along the "
"way.\n"
"<big>III.</big>\n"
"After casting a trap-style spell (Bane and Capture) you must right-click "
"anywhere within 4 hexes of your unit and select 'Place Bane/Capture Trap' to "
"place the trap there."
msgstr ""

#
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Back"
msgstr "Voltar"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "Experience"
msgstr "Experiência"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<big>IV.</big>\n"
"Experience is gained by doing good deeds and following the code of the "
"brotherhood. If you break the code you may lose experience.\n"
"<big>V.</big>\n"
"When a mage advances, his maximum mana level is increased by 4 and a new "
"spell can be chosen by right-clicking on the mage and choosing 'Character "
"Advancement'.\n"
"<big>VI.</big>\n"
"At certain times you may find yourself in control of additional units. Your "
"mage gains experience whenever one of these units advances.\n"
"<big>VII.</big>\n"
"If your mage dies another player can bring you back with the level 4 healing "
"spell, 'Reincarnation'."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [option]: speaker=narrator
msgid "General Tips"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
msgid ""
"<big>VIII.</big>\n"
"Each mage can only carry one extra weapon and one suit of armour. These can "
"be bought and sold in shops.\n"
"<big>IX.</big>\n"
"The scenario is fairly non-linear, so sometimes it is worth returning to "
"areas you've already explored. Also, some parts of it will be too tough for "
"inexperienced mages.\n"
"<big>X.</big>\n"
"If a player seems to be taking a long time to end their turn, it may be "
"because they are reading dialogue or deciding on an option.\n"
"<big>XI.</big>\n"
"You can switch the sides of a unit you control by right-clicking on it.\n"
"<big>XII.</big>\n"
"If you are bothered by long delays at the beginning of your turns, try the :"
"nosaves command to disable autosaving.\n"
"<big>XIII.</big>\n"
"Although you'll cover more ground by travelling seperately, you are in "
"danger whenever the party is divided. Stay close and work together!"
msgstr ""

